(4, 'CLT-576154-2025-001', 'Forensic Imaging, Extraction, Indexing and Keyword searches of 3 laptops belonging to:\r\n\r\na) Katlego Mashishi,\r\nb) Kelebogile Magano, and\r\nc) Ernest'),
(5, 'CLT-MUT001-2025-001', '1.1	Our telephone conversation on 14 February 2025 refers.\r\n1.2	You have indicated that the Deputy Vice-Chancellor (DVC) responsible for student accommodation has sourced student accommodation without following proper process.\r\n1.3	As a result, you sent the DVC [responsible for student accommodation] an email highlighting the same.\r\n1.4	After a few days that you had sent this email, you searched for it in your inbox and could not locate it.\r\n1.5	You have also indicated that you noticed a few emails that you had sent to a few other people also disappeared. \r\n1.6	You noticed this event on two occasions, in the second occasion that this happened, you were out of the country.\r\n1.7	You suspect that someone has deleted these emails from your inbox and as a result would like to determine the account that was used to delete these emails and wherever possible retrieve the deleted emails.'),
(6, 'CLT-REH001-2025-001', '1.1	Our Microsoft Teams meeting on 15 May 2025 refers.\r\n1.2	You have recently experienced a series of security-related incidents suggesting a systemic breakdown in cybersecurity controls, internal information governance, and communication protocols.\r\n1.3	These incidents span several areas of concern, indicating both external threats and internal vulnerabilities.\r\n1.4	There have been multiple cases of unauthorised access to company funds, along with leaks of confidential data, including internal proposals and Microsoft Teams communications.\r\n1.5	These leaks appear to be linked to suspicious email activity, originating from compromised internal accounts.\r\n1.6	Following your organisation’s implementation of Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) on April 2, there were still several unauthorised login attempts recorded between April 15 and 17.\r\n1.7	These attempts specifically targeted high-value systems, including Microsoft Exchange, Outlook, and other business-critical applications, suggesting deliberate efforts to bypass security enhancements.\r\n1.8	You also encountered email-based threats and extortion. Fraudulent invoices were sent using spoofed or compromised email addresses, resulting in unauthorised financial transactions.\r\n1.9	One particularly serious incident involved an extortion demand threatening the deletion of your website, which was subsequently taken offline and only restored following payment.\r\n1.10	Further concerns have arisen around potential insider threats. One staff member demonstrated access to historical system logs from as far back as 2014–2016 and appeared to have leaked sensitive employee termination and financial data.\r\n1.11	Suspicious behaviour patterns, including unmonitored WhatsApp communications, point to deeper issues around internal access and trust.\r\n1.12	In the course of your review, you identified security control gaps and policy violations. Some user accounts remained active for former employees or unused devices.\r\n1.13	MFA and other access policies were applied inconsistently across departments.\r\n1.14	As a precaution, you had to disable Gmail access due to unverified external communications and suspicious usage patterns.\r\n1.15	There have been troubling instances of data integrity breaches. Passwords were changed without authorisation, locking out legitimate users.\r\n1.16	Internal systems were accessed without proper clearance, and inconsistencies were found in email signatures, payment records, and invoice validation—raising strong indications of manipulation and impersonation.\r\n1.17	These developments suggest a coordinated and multifaceted exposure to cyber risk, with vulnerabilities spanning technical, procedural, and human factors.\r\n1.18	 Immediate attention, forensic investigation, and corrective action are necessary to restore control, contain the impact, and prevent future incidents.'),
(7, 'CLT-REH001-2025-002', 'Forensic Imaging of 3 Devices'),
(8, 'CLT-BAG001-2025-001', 'Forensic Imaging of two devices, a cellphone and laptop.');

